<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><B normal? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-weight:><FONT size=2><FONT face="Century Gothic"><FONT color=#ff0000>Solution suggestions<namespace prefix = o ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"></FONT></FONT></FONT></B></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt 0in 0.5in; -0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 mso-list: l0 **SMURF**?MARGIN:><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Gothic?? ?Century **SMURF**?mso-fareast-font-family: Gothic?;><SPAN Ignore? **SMURF**?mso-list:><FONT face="Century Gothic" size=2>1)</FONT><SPAN New ?Times Roman?? 7pt **SMURF**?FONT:>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:><FONT size=2>Raise all beastlord skill caps up to 250 just like HtH is currently.</FONT></SPAN></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt 0in 0.5in; -0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 mso-list: l0 **SMURF**?MARGIN:><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Gothic?? ?Century **SMURF**?mso-fareast-font-family: Gothic?;><SPAN Ignore? **SMURF**?mso-list:><FONT face="Century Gothic" size=2>2)</FONT><SPAN New ?Times Roman?? 7pt **SMURF**?FONT:>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN><FONT size=2><B normal? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-weight:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:>(A) </SPAN></B><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:>Make it so that pet buffs show their remaining duration just like player character buffs now do. <B normal? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-weight:>(B) </B>Allow the player to click off buffs (non-detrimental of course) from their warder's buff box just like they can their own.</SPAN></FONT></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt 0in 0.5in; -0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 mso-list: l0 **SMURF**?MARGIN:><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Gothic?? ?Century **SMURF**?mso-fareast-font-family: Gothic?;><SPAN Ignore? **SMURF**?mso-list:><FONT face="Century Gothic" size=2>3)</FONT><SPAN New ?Times Roman?? 7pt **SMURF**?FONT:>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN><FONT size=2><B normal? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-weight:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:>(A) </SPAN></B><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:>Look into DoT agro. As it stands now the ratio of damage to agro on many of these spells is far to high both before and after focus/AA are considered. This is not a beastlord specific issue by any means as shaman and Necromancers have similar problems.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN><B normal? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-weight:>(B) </B>Make future AAs more in line with how Beastlords work. That means more spell crit AAs and AAs that add damage without adding extra agro.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN><B normal? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-weight:>(C) </B>Consider adding a disc to Beastlords similar to what warriors got except instead of increasing hate, have it lower hate.</SPAN></FONT></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt 0in 0.5in; -0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 mso-list: l0 **SMURF**?MARGIN:><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Gothic?? ?Century **SMURF**?mso-fareast-font-family: Gothic?;><SPAN Ignore? **SMURF**?mso-list:><FONT face="Century Gothic" size=2>4)</FONT><SPAN New ?Times Roman?? 7pt **SMURF**?FONT:>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:><FONT size=2>Lower the casting on Sorsha. This makes it possible to actually have the heal land in the situations where you would be using it. With the lower casting time Beastlords would understand a recast time being added to the spell so that our sustained healing per second and our efficiency didn't change from what it currently is. Our intention isn't to improve the spell as much as it is to simply make it functional.</FONT></SPAN></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt 0in 0.5in; -0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 mso-list: l0 **SMURF**?MARGIN:><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Gothic?? ?Century **SMURF**?mso-fareast-font-family: Gothic?;><SPAN Ignore? **SMURF**?mso-list:><FONT face="Century Gothic" size=2>5)</FONT><SPAN New ?Times Roman?? 7pt **SMURF**?FONT:>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN><FONT size=2><B normal? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-weight:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:>(A) </SPAN></B><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:>Please improve the range of feral swipe a bit more.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>The first change fixed most of the issues, but there are still some fights where the skill simply can't be used.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN><B normal? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-weight:>(B) </B>Raise the hit% on feral swipe and give it higher minimum damage. Most are happy with not having to spam feral swipe like they do kick, but with feral swipes current hit% and it's damage range the skill simply doesn't do enough damage to warrant the 9AA and the hot key space.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN><B normal? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-weight:>(C) </B>Raise the damage on feral swipe and have it lock out kick. This keeps the AA as the DPS booster it was, but allows it to take the place of kick. Thus just swapping out the kick hot key for the new feral swipe one. Having the new skill average out to being a bit more damage than feral swipe + kick now does would be great.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN><B normal? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-weight:>(D) </B>Forget the DPS portion of feral swipe and turn this skill into a means of lowering beastlord agro. Some Beastlords would rather give up the ~1dps feral swipe currently does and simply have the skill turned into a DE-agro skill for Beastlords.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>If this were done then the skill would have to have its refresh changed and always land, etc.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></FONT></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt 0in 0.5in; -0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 mso-list: l0 **SMURF**?MARGIN:><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Gothic?? ?Century **SMURF**?mso-fareast-font-family: Gothic?;><SPAN Ignore? **SMURF**?mso-list:><FONT face="Century Gothic" size=2>6)</FONT><SPAN New ?Times Roman?? 7pt **SMURF**?FONT:>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN><FONT size=2><B normal? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-weight:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:>(A) </SPAN></B><SPAN **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family: Gothic?? ?Century><FONT face="Century Gothic">Have the pet naturally move at a faster rate.</FONT></SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:> <B normal? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-weight:>(B) </B></SPAN><FONT face="Century Gothic"><SPAN **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family: Gothic?? ?Century>Have the pet take on the AA run speed that the owner has.</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt 0in 0.5in; -0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 mso-list: l0 **SMURF**?MARGIN:><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Gothic?? ?Century **SMURF**?mso-fareast-font-family: Gothic?;><SPAN Ignore? **SMURF**?mso-list:><FONT face="Century Gothic" size=2>7)</FONT><SPAN New ?Times Roman?? 7pt **SMURF**?FONT:>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN><FONT size=2><B normal? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-weight:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:>(A) </SPAN></B><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:>Let suspended pets zone.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN><B normal? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-weight:>(B) </B>Have a check to see if the player has a pet currently out or not. If the player does already have one pet out then poof the suspended pet upon zoning.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>If the player doesn't have a pet out, then simply let the suspended pet zone. This would keep the player limited to 1 pet well zoning, but would let them zone well invisibility and zone after losing invisibility without trying to un-suspend their pet.</SPAN></FONT></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt 0in 0.5in; -0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 mso-list: l0 **SMURF**?MARGIN:><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Gothic?? ?Century **SMURF**?mso-fareast-font-family: Gothic?;><SPAN Ignore? **SMURF**?mso-list:><FONT face="Century Gothic" size=2>8)</FONT><SPAN New ?Times Roman?? 7pt **SMURF**?FONT:>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN><FONT size=2><B normal? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-weight:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:>(A) </SPAN></B><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:>Allow all proc buffs to overwrite each other.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN><B normal? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-weight:>(B) </B>Allow hobble of spirits to stack with other beastlord proc buffs.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN><B normal? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-weight:>(C) </B>Add a second rank to hobble that gives the snare proc a DD component as well.</SPAN></FONT></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt 0in 0.5in; -0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 mso-list: l0 **SMURF**?MARGIN:><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Gothic?? ?Century **SMURF**?mso-fareast-font-family: Gothic?;><SPAN Ignore? **SMURF**?mso-list:><FONT face="Century Gothic" size=2>9)</FONT><SPAN New ?Times Roman?? 7pt **SMURF**?FONT:>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:><FONT size=2>Change the spell to match the current heals rangers get. Beastlords and rangers have had identical heal/regen spells at the same levels since Beastlords went into the game. With Gates this suddenly changed with no explanation. If it's intended that Beastlords directly heal worse than rangers do because of the Shaman/Druid relationship, then please consider a heal over time spell. </FONT></SPAN></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt 0in 0.5in; -0.25in; TEXT-INDENT: .5in? list tab-stops: lfo1; level1 mso-list: l0 **SMURF**?MARGIN:><FONT color=#ff0000><SPAN mso-bidi-font-family: Gothic?? ?Century **SMURF**?mso-fareast-font-family: Gothic?;><SPAN Ignore? **SMURF**?mso-list:><FONT face="Century Gothic" size=2>10)</FONT><SPAN New ?Times Roman?? 7pt **SMURF**?FONT:>&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></SPAN><FONT size=2><FONT face="Century Gothic"><SPAN **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family: Gothic?? ?Century>Fix the AA back to how it previously was please; there is really no other way to say it. Currently Beastlords/Bards are losing 15% of their off-hand damage and ~6% of their total melee damage because of this bug.<SPAN yes? **SMURF**?mso-spacerun:>&nbsp; </SPAN>This same issue is also on the bard top 10 list.</SPAN><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:></SPAN></FONT></FONT></FONT></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0pt 0.25in? 0in **SMURF**?MARGIN:><SPAN Verdana? **SMURF**?FONT-FAMILY:><BR><BR><BR><BR line-break? **SMURF**?mso-special-character:><BR line-break? **SMURF**?mso-special-character:><FONT face="Century Gothic" color=#ff0000 size=2></FONT></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal 0in 0pt? **SMURF**?MARGIN:><FONT face="Century Gothic" color=#ff0000 size=2>&nbsp;</FONT></P>
<P><FONT color=#ff0000></FONT>&nbsp;</P>
