<DIV><STRONG>Details on Beastlord list #1 part A</STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>All throughout beta there were three PH spells for Beastlords that at the end of beta simply poofed.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>There have been many suggestions made for what spells could be added...<namespace prefix = o ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"></SPAN></P>
<UL type=disc **SMURF**?MARGIN-TOP: 0in?>
<LI class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: l1 none; mso-list: level1 tab-stops: list .5in? lfo1;><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>A new slow spell at 70.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>Keep the slow % the same as Shaman’s revenge, but add a negative resist mod to the spell.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>Beastlords are having a hard time slowing in a growing number of places.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>One of the main things we bring to a group is the ability to slow, but we simply aren't performing it to a reasonable degree in certain spots.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>There are times where a beastlord can chain cast slow and never get it to stick before a mob dies.</SPAN> 
<LI class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: l1 none; mso-list: level1 tab-stops: list .5in? lfo1;><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>A self only buff.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>The only self-only buff Beastlords get is "frenzy" a low level shaman spell that we got back at level 49.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>Some of the main suggestions for this buff are: +double atk mod, +dmg mod, +avoidance mod, +mana regen.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN>
<LI class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: l1 none; mso-list: level1 tab-stops: list .5in? lfo1;><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>A new debuff<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>Our last debuff was incapacitate at level 56.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>Either upgrading the line or adding a new type of Beastlord debuff that stacked with other debuffs would be a nice addition to our current omens line up.</SPAN> 
<LI class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: l1 none; mso-list: level1 tab-stops: list .5in? lfo1;><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>A de-agro type of spell.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>Beastlords simply generate too much agro for the damage they are doing.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>We are the only melee in the game outside of paladins and warriors that don't get some way (via AA or skill) to lower our agro.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp;</SPAN></SPAN> 
<LI class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: l1 none; mso-list: level1 tab-stops: list .5in? lfo1;><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:><SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>Group infusion of spirit.&nbsp; This spell was highly requested by beastlords, but where it came from in GoD made it almost useless to those that could actually get it.&nbsp; Now that omens is out and the stat caps are going up again a lot of beastlords could use the spell if it were put at level 66.</SPAN></SPAN></LI></UL></DIV></DIV>
