			>
			<DIV></DIV>
<DIV>
<DIV><STRONG>Details on&nbsp;#1 part b -</STRONG> </DIV>
<DIV><STRONG><U>Spells received in Omens - </U></STRONG></DIV>
<DIV>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:><STRONG>Healing of Mikkily -</STRONG></SPAN><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:> This is our new pet heal and just like sorsha before it the usefulness of this spell is very low because of the casting time on the spell. <SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp;</SPAN>Beastlords are a melee class and having a casting time that long simply doesn't work for the class.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>On paper the spell looks great in terms of mana ratio and healing, but in actual practice many Beastlords don't even memorize their pet heal.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN><namespace prefix = o ns = "http://www.lithium.com/unique/URI"></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:><STRONG><SPAN **SMURF**?mso-tab-count: 1?>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN>Possible solution:</STRONG></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>Lower the casting time on this spell (and healing of Sorsha) to ~4 seconds.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>If this is deemed too powerful then please feel free to add a recast time that will keep our current healing per second the same.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>Beastlords don't want to heal better or heal more they just want to actual consider healing at all.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>As it stands now you have many Beastlords that don't even memorize their pet heal because in almost every situation they'd use it the casting time is just too long.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:><STRONG>Chimera Blood -</STRONG></SPAN><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:> Another spell that has a major issue from our top 10 list.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>Beastlord agro is very high in terms of dmg done to agro generated.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>Before omens you had many Beastlords that were unable to use scorpion venom because of the high agro it generated for the damage done.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>Fights in EQ don't last very long and in order for this DOT to be mana efficient you have to land it early.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>Having chimera blood actually add even more counters than scorpion venom is very bad.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:><STRONG><SPAN **SMURF**?mso-tab-count: 1?>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN>Possible solutions:</STRONG></SPAN></P>
<UL type=disc **SMURF**?MARGIN-TOP: 0in?>
<LI class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: lfo2; none; mso-list: level1 tab-stops: list .5in? l0><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>Fix DOTs.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>DOTs are very out of line compared to nukes and other forms of damage in modern day EQ.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN>
<LI class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: lfo2; none; mso-list: level1 tab-stops: list .5in? l0><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>Add a minus hate component to this spell that will allow it to be used for now.</SPAN></LI></UL>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:><STRONG>Spiritual Ascendance</STRONG></SPAN><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:><STRONG> - </STRONG>This is definitely a defining spell for Beastlords.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>The line has always improved by +2 hp/mana per tick.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>Now suddenly in omens we see a boost of +1 hp/mana per tick.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>This is an extremely minor gain and if you look at the numbers you'd see that by having a constant gain to the line like we've had instead of a % based gain that we get less and less each upgrade as it is...</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>SL to SR = 66% upgrade</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>SR to SP = 40% upgrade</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>SP to SD = 29% upgrade</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>SD to SA(at 10) = 11% upgrade</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>SD to SA(at 11) = 22% upgrade </SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>The other big issue with the entire spiritual line of hp/mana regen is the base duration. Even with SCR3 and an extended enhancement item a beastlord can't sustain MGB'n the spell on a raid.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:><SPAN **SMURF**?mso-tab-count: 1?>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;<STRONG>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </STRONG></SPAN><STRONG>Possible solutions:</STRONG></SPAN></P>
<UL type=disc **SMURF**?MARGIN-TOP: 0in?>
<LI class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none; mso-list: level1 tab-stops: list .5in? lfo3; l3><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>Raise the regen to 11/11 instead of the 10/10 it's at now. </SPAN>
<LI class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none; mso-list: level1 tab-stops: list .5in? lfo3; l3><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>Raise the base duration of the spell.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>An hour twelve base like our hp/atk line has would be ideal.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>Beastlords would understand an increase in mana cost if this change were to go in.</SPAN></LI></UL>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:><STRONG>Festering Malady -</STRONG></SPAN><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:> This is our current level 70 disease DOT.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>Simply put this isn't a Beastlord level 70 spell it's a mid-50's level shaman spell.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>The duration on the DOT is far too long, the casting time isn't what it should be, and the damage needs to be changed as well.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>What happened is this spell was made as an upgrade to plague because that is the spell we were given at level 65.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>The problem is at 65 we should have been given a beastlord only disease DOT that was an upgrade to malaria (our level 44 disease DOT). </SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>Since the spell didn't cost a rune we didn't really complain and let it go.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>If you actually look at beastlord DOTs though you'll see that festering malady as it stands now simply doesn't belong.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>First of all festering malady has a 6.1 casting time. </SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>This is clearly left over from the copy/paste of a shaman spell.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>If you look at malaria you'll see it's a 3.0 casting time.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>Also, if you look at scorpion venom (our level 61 DOT) that is basically a copy of envenomed bolt you'll see that has a casting time of 4.1 instead of the 6.1 of Ebolt.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>Next is the actual duration of the DOT.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>Beastlords are unable to use their poison DOTs in most situations because of the high agro on them and the duration on festering malady makes it useless in many situations as well.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:><SPAN **SMURF**?mso-tab-count: 1?>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN>Possible solution:</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>Make this into a beastlord spell instead of keeping it as a very weak shaman spell that simply doesn't fit Beastlords.</SPAN></P>
<UL type=disc **SMURF**?MARGIN-TOP: 0in?>
<LI class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none; mso-list: level1 tab-stops: list .5in? lfo4; l5><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>Lower the casting time </SPAN>
<LI class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none; mso-list: level1 tab-stops: list .5in? lfo4; l5><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>Lower the duration to 9 ticks</SPAN> 
<LI class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none; mso-list: level1 tab-stops: list .5in? lfo4; l5><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>Raise the damage per tick up so that the total damage of the spell is about the same as it is now, but in fewer ticks</SPAN></LI></UL>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>These changes will make the spell into an actual beastlord spell that we'll memorize and be able to use in various situations.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:><STRONG>Ferocity of Irionu –</STRONG> </SPAN><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>This is another of our level 70 spells.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>This is an upgrade to Ferocity.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>I'm just going to post the spell data on Ferocity and then on ferocity of Irionu and go from there...</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:><STRONG>Ferocity</STRONG></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>5:<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN><SPAN **SMURF**?mso-tab-count: 1?>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN>Increase STA by 40</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>7: <SPAN **SMURF**?mso-tab-count: 1?>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN>Increase ATK by 150</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>8: <SPAN **SMURF**?mso-tab-count: 1?>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN>Increase All Resists by 65</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:><STRONG>Ferocity of Irionu</STRONG></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>5:<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN><SPAN **SMURF**?mso-tab-count: 1?>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN>Increase STA by 52</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>7: <SPAN **SMURF**?mso-tab-count: 1?>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN>Increase ATK by 187</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>8: <SPAN **SMURF**?mso-tab-count: 1?>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN>Increase All Resists by 65</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>Both spells have a 6.5 min base duration a 3.0 casting time and a 2 minute recast time.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>Ferocity costs 600 mana well Ferocity of Irionu costs 750 mana.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>That means that we pay 150 more mana so that we can add +12 sta and +37 atk for a very short period of time.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>The stamina is really weak on its own because of how stats cap and how the diminishing returns on hps per sta. <SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp;</SPAN>The atk boost is very minor for the mana cost and the resists don't change.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>&nbsp;</SPAN><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>It's clear that looking at this line of spells that it was designed to be a short duration, mana intensive buff that boosted: Hit points, melee damage, and spell resistance.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>Sadly this last installment in the line falls woefully short.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>Some combination of the below suggestions would make this spell into something that Beastlords would both use and desire.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>Please remember this is a level 70 rune for us and one of the few unique things a beastlord actually brings to a group or raid.</SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:><STRONG><SPAN **SMURF**?mso-tab-count: 1?>&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp;&nbsp; </SPAN>Possible solutions:</STRONG></SPAN></P>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:><STRONG>For the +sta part:</STRONG></SPAN></P>
<UL type=disc **SMURF**?MARGIN-TOP: 0in?>
<LI class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none; mso-list: level1 tab-stops: list .5in? lfo5; l4><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>Remove the +sta from the buff and add a +raw hp component that stacks with everything.<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>The simply truth is that many won't get any hps at all from ferocity of irionu and those that do will gain very few.</SPAN></LI></UL>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:><STRONG>For the +atk part:</STRONG></SPAN></P>
<UL type=disc **SMURF**?MARGIN-TOP: 0in?>
<LI class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none; mso-list: level1 tab-stops: list .5in? lfo5; l4><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>Raise the amount of atk added by the spell.</SPAN> 
<LI class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none; mso-list: level1 tab-stops: list .5in? lfo5; l4><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>Add a modifier to the spell that offers some other melee enhancing effect such as:<SPAN **SMURF**?mso-spacerun: yes?>&nbsp; </SPAN>+double attack, +crits, +accuracy, etc.</SPAN></LI></UL>
<P class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none?><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:><STRONG>For the Resist portion:</STRONG></SPAN></P>
<UL type=disc **SMURF**?MARGIN-TOP: 0in?>
<LI class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none; mso-list: level1 tab-stops: list .5in? l2 lfo6;><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>Allow the resists from the spell to break the resist cap.</SPAN> 
<LI class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none; mso-list: level1 tab-stops: list .5in? l2 lfo6;><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>Add an effect similar to what bestial alignment has like +chance to resist spell</SPAN> 
<LI class=MsoNormal **SMURF**?MARGIN: 0in 0pt; mso-layout-grid-align: none; mso-list: level1 tab-stops: list .5in? l2 lfo6;><SPAN ?Century Gothic?? **SMURF**?mso-bidi-font-family:>Add an effect like +spell shield to it</SPAN></LI></UL></DIV></DIV>
